description.narrative: Through UNICEF support, coverage of essential newborn care services increased from 11 (2019) to 23 (2020) health facilities. To strengthen open-defecation-free communities, UNICEF provided support towards certifying from 21 per cent to 64 per cent of the triggered communities. UNICEF supported training of all maternity facilities on Infection Prevention Control on COVID-19. To contribute towards prevention of mother to child transmission of HIV, community follow up and support system for HIV-infected mothers and their infants was enhanced. UNICEF procured nutrition supplies as well as disseminated information on infant feeding and on young child feeding to the most vulnerable peri-urban community. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:11/01/2021
